The paper proposes a new neural network architecture for policy representation in deep reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. The paper focuses on improving control tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. However, the proposed architecture is a neural network, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper mentions using the proposed architecture for vision-based tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category. Overall, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.CV, in that order.
